info.author: tight.ai
info.description:
Tight.ai SDK

The Tight.ai SDK is a simple and effective way to deploy your machine learning models to production with tight.ai.

Built with ♥ in Southern California.

```console pip install tightai --upgrade ``` ## Models ### Create `tightai.models.create()` ```python my_model = tightai.models.create( name="Spam vs Ham", slug="spam-vs-ham", model_type="text", framework="tightai.frameworks.keras" ) ``` ### Get `tightai.models.get()` ```python my_model = tightai.models.get( slug="spam-vs-ham", ) ``` ### List `tightai.models.all()` ```python my_models = tightai.models.all() ``` ### Upload Version Uploading a version of your model requires a sample. This method verifies the model prior to uploading. #### Text Model `tightai.models.upload(model_type='text')` ```python import os import tightai text_classifer_data = { "sample": "Hello World", "model_path": "/path/to/export/model.h5", "metadata": { "classes": ["spam", "ham"], "max_length": 130 }, "model_type": "text", "tokenizer_path": "/path/to/export/tokenizer.pkl", "version": 1, "framework": "tightai.frameworks.Keras" } my_model.upload(**text_classifer) ``` #### Image Model `tightai.models.upload(model_type='image')` ```python import os import tightai image_classifer_data = { "sample": "/path/to/samples/myimage.jpg", "model_path": "/path/to/export/model.h5", "metadata": { "classes": ["hot-dog", "not-hot-dog"] }, "model_type": "image", "version": 1, "framework": "tightai.frameworks.Keras" } img_model = tightai.models.create( name="Hot Dog vs Not Hot Dog", slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog", model_type="image", framework="tightai.frameworks.keras" ) img_model.upload(**image_classifer_data) ``` ### Predict (Locally) The below methods will download (if needed) a local copy of a model and run the prediction. `tightai.models.predict()` ```python local_img_path = '/path/to/image.jpg' img_model = tightai.models.predict( local_img_path, slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog", version=1 ) ``` `my_model.predict()` ```python text_model = tightai.models.get(slug="spam-vs-ham") text_model.predict("Want a juice box and some string cheese?") ``` ### Deploy A deployed model is accessible by the outside world. `tightai.models.deploy()` ```python tightai.models.deploy(slug="spam-vs-ham", version=1) ``` `my_model.deploy()` ```python img_model = tightai.models.get(slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog"") img_model.deploy(version=1) ``` ----- ## Deployments ### Create Use models methods below. ### Get `tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham')` ### List `tightai.deployments.all()` ### Predict `tightai.deployments.get().predict()` ``` text_model = tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham') text_model.predict("Winter is coming") ``` ----- ## Predict **Model Slug** (local) `tightai.predict(model='spam-vs-ham')` ```python tightai.predict("Winter is coming", model='spam-vs-ham') ``` **Deployment Slug** `tightai.predict(deployment='spam-vs-ham')` ```python tightai.predict("Winter is here", deployment='spam-vs-ham') ``` **Deployment Endpoint** `tightai.predict(endpoint='spam-vs-ham')` ```python text_model = tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham') tightai.predict("Winter was pretty mild. Summer is coming.", endpoint=text_model.endpoint) ``` ----- ### Supported Frameworks: We currently support: - [Keras](https://keras.io/) with [Tensorflow](https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/keras) > More coming soon, check https://www.tight.ai/blog for more. **Get Available Frameworks** ```python tightai.frameworks.get_available(verbose=True) ``` #### Keras Using [Tensorflow](https://www.tensorflow.org/guide/keras) backend. ##### Text Classification (`tightai.frameworks.keras.KerasText`) ##### Image Classification (`tightai.frameworks.keras.KerasImage`)
info.name: tightai
info.html_description:
Tight.ai SDK

The Tight.ai SDK is a simple and effective way to deploy your machine learning models to production with tight.ai.

Built with ♥ in Southern California.

pip install tightai --upgrade

Models

Create

tightai.models.create()

my_model = tightai.models.create(
    name="Spam vs Ham",
    slug="spam-vs-ham",
    model_type="text",
    framework="tightai.frameworks.keras"
)

Get

tightai.models.get()

my_model = tightai.models.get(
    slug="spam-vs-ham",
)

List

tightai.models.all()

my_models = tightai.models.all()

Upload Version

Uploading a version of your model requires a sample. This method verifies the model prior to uploading.

Text Model

tightai.models.upload(model_type='text')

import os
import tightai

text_classifer_data = {
    "sample": "Hello World",
    "model_path": "/path/to/export/model.h5",
    "metadata": {
        "classes": ["spam", "ham"], 
        "max_length": 130
    },
    "model_type": "text",
    "tokenizer_path": "/path/to/export/tokenizer.pkl",
    "version": 1,
    "framework": "tightai.frameworks.Keras"
}

my_model.upload(**text_classifer)

Image Model

tightai.models.upload(model_type='image')

import os
import tightai

image_classifer_data = {
    "sample": "/path/to/samples/myimage.jpg",
    "model_path": "/path/to/export/model.h5",
    "metadata": {
        "classes": ["hot-dog", "not-hot-dog"]
    },
    "model_type": "image",
    "version": 1,
    "framework": "tightai.frameworks.Keras"
}

img_model = tightai.models.create(
    name="Hot Dog vs Not Hot Dog",
    slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog",
    model_type="image",
    framework="tightai.frameworks.keras"
)
img_model.upload(**image_classifer_data)

Predict (Locally)

The below methods will download (if needed) a local copy of a model and run the prediction.

tightai.models.predict()

local_img_path = '/path/to/image.jpg'
img_model = tightai.models.predict(
    local_img_path,
    slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog",
    version=1
)

my_model.predict()

text_model = tightai.models.get(slug="spam-vs-ham")
text_model.predict("Want a juice box and some string cheese?")

Deploy

A deployed model is accessible by the outside world.

tightai.models.deploy()

tightai.models.deploy(slug="spam-vs-ham", version=1)

my_model.deploy()

img_model = tightai.models.get(slug="hot-dog-not-hot-dog"")
img_model.deploy(version=1)

Deployments

Create

Use models methods below.

Get

tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham')

List

tightai.deployments.all()

Predict

tightai.deployments.get().predict()

text_model = tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham')
text_model.predict("Winter is coming")

Predict

Model Slug (local) tightai.predict(model='spam-vs-ham')

tightai.predict("Winter is coming", model='spam-vs-ham')

Deployment Slug tightai.predict(deployment='spam-vs-ham')

tightai.predict("Winter is here", deployment='spam-vs-ham')

Deployment Endpoint tightai.predict(endpoint='spam-vs-ham')

text_model = tightai.deployments.get(slug='spam-vs-ham')
tightai.predict("Winter was pretty mild. Summer is coming.", endpoint=text_model.endpoint)

Supported Frameworks:

We currently support:

  • Keras with Tensorflow

More coming soon, check https://www.tight.ai/blog for more.

Get Available Frameworks

tightai.frameworks.get_available(verbose=True)

Keras

Using Tensorflow backend.

Text Classification (tightai.frameworks.keras.KerasText)
Image Classification (tightai.frameworks.keras.KerasImage)
